benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogs - Retrieve audit logs by account id

covered: Valid Request: Successful retrieval for existing account
Empty Response: Account with no audit logs returns empty array
Query Parameters: Extra query parameters ignored scenario
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid authentication tokens (401)
Error Handling: 404 for non-existent account, 400/422 for invalid accountId, 500 for system errors
System/Performance Consideration: Large number of audit logs scenario and response time check
Regression: Empty audit logs scenario regression test
Backward compatibility: Older client version does not break response
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for paginating large audit log lists
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting ETag/Cache-Control or other caching headers
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No explicit test for handling many requests per short interval
Authorization edge cases: No test explicitly covering 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions or role-based access
Input Validation depth: Some edge cases like empty accountId in TC15 exist, but broader input validation scenarios could be expanded
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to validate page size, page tokens, and total counts for large datasets
Add caching header validations (ETag, Cache-Control) to ensure proper client-side caching behavior
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to verify system behavior under bursty traffic
Add authorization edge-case tests for 403 Forbidden when user lacks permissions
Enhance input validation coverage for accountId formats and edge cases (empty, extremely long, special characters) including explicit negative tests
